Sources and contributions
-------------------------
- The underlying text is the Encyclopædia Britannica, Eleventh Edition
  (1910–1911), which is in the PUBLIC DOMAIN (published before 1929). The
  raw text may therefore also be used on its own public-domain terms.
- The transcription of that text is courtesy of Wikisource
  (https://en.wikisource.org/wiki/1911_Encyclopædia_Britannica) and the
  Internet Archive.
- The Markdown rendering, the resolved cross-reference graph, the
  machine-readable subject taxonomy (reconstructed from the printed index
  volume), and the resolved authorship graph are the contribution of this
  project, and it is these that CC-BY-SA 4.0 governs.
